<recipe 
xmlns="https://cazzscookingcommunity.github.io" 
xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" 
xsi:schemaLocation="https://cazzscookingcommunity.github.io /xml/recipe.xsd"> 
                                                                                
    <title>Upside Down Banana Cake</title>
    <filename>upside_down_banana_cake.xml</filename>

    <comment></comment>
    <thumbnail>../images/placeholder.png</thumbnail>
    <image></image>
    <category></category>
    <yield></yield>
    <prepTime></prepTime>
    <cookTime></cookTime>



    <part>
        <ingredient>75gms butter</ingredient>
        <ingredient>1/4 cup sugar</ingredient>
        <ingredient>1/4 cup brown sugar</ingredient>
        <ingredient>1 teasp vanilla essence</ingredient>
        <ingredient>1/2 teasp baking soda </ingredient>
        <ingredient>4 bananas cut in half</ingredient>
        <ingredient>3/4 cup plain flour</ingredient>
        <ingredient>1/2 teasp baking powder</ingredient>
        <ingredient>1/4 cup coconut</ingredient>
        <ingredient>1/4 milk</ingredient>
        <ingredient>1 egg</ingredient>
        <step>Turn on oven to 160C.</step>
        <step>Prepare a baking dish by greasing it with butter and set aside. </step>
        <step>Melt butter for sauce in a small pan. Once completely melted add the sugar. Stir until melted. </step>
        <step>Pour in prepared dish, then place cut bananas on top, set aside. </step>
    
        <step>Beat butter in mixer until light. Add sugars and beat for 5 minutes. Add egg and vanilla essence and beat until combine. </step>
        <step>Add flour, coconut and baking soda then lastly milk. Beat until combined and push down sides a few times. </step>
        <step>Spoon over bananas and flatten with a large spoon. </step>
        <step>Place in oven for 30 minutes or until top is golden. </step>
        <step>Turn upside down on a dish and serve with ice cream or cream, if desired.</step>
    </part>

    <part>
        <title>Sauce</title>
        <ingredient>100gms butter</ingredient>
        <ingredient>1/2 cup brown sugar</ingredient>
    </part>

</recipe>